Night Club Features

Customer Ratings:
    
    1:
    2:
    3:
    4:
    5:

Disco Hours;
    Early Evening (8pm-10pm)
    Mid Evening (10pm-12am)
    Peak Hours (12am-2pm)
    Late Night (2pm-Closing)
    
Customer Behaviours and needs;
    Early Evening
        Customers:
            Early arrivals for casual drinks or to reserve tables.
        Atmosphere:
            Softer quite music, less crowd.
    
    Mid Evening:
        Customer:
            Group of people arrivals for drinks. (more people wants to drinks)
            Dance Floor attracts more people.
        Atmosphere:
            Music volume and energy increases.
            
    Peak Hours:
        Customer:
            All Customers Arrive
            Heavy bar traffic.
            Dance Floor is packed.
            Bottle Service.
        Atmosphere:
            Music is loud and energized, light are intense
                
    Late Hours:
        Customer:
            People starts to leave
        Atmosphere:
            Music may stay high energy vibe depends how crowd the club is.
            
           
Features:
    Resevation for big group of people (Drop notification for player)